{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Preheat oven to 160°C. Line a 12-hole muffin tray with paper cases and set aside.","Place polenta, sugar and citrus zests into mixing bowl and mill <b>30 sec\/speed 9<b>.","Add butter, vanilla, 1 tablespoon of the lemon juice and 1 tablespoon of the lime juice (see Tips) into mixing bowl and mix <b>10 sec\/speed 5<b>.","Add eggs, flour and baking powder and mix <b>10 sec\/speed 4<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula, folding through any uncombined mixture.","Transfer mixture into prepared paper cases. Bake for 20-25 minutes (160°C), or until a skewer inserted into the centre of the cakes comes out clean. Allow to cool in tin for 5-10 minutes, then transfer onto a wire rack to cool completely before serving."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["180 g polenta (see Tips)","180 g raw sugar","2 lemons, zest (no white pith) and juice","1 lime, zest (no white pith) and juice","200 g butter, cut into pieces (2 cm)","1 tsp natural vanilla extract","4 eggs","60 g spelt flour","2 tsp baking powder"]}],"id":"r135072","imageLink":"https:\/\/1.bp.blogspot.com\/-Qw9QOoNvrn4\/XZWptlydN6I\/AAAAAAAAfN4\/ytDR213wQJoWk98qZGh5d4yIf0_5F55_gCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_3jW6twI8bEIEntZN.png","title":"Lemon and lime polenta cakes","publishedAt":"2017-04-02T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"4.4 g","fat":"15.6 g","uom":"per 1 portions","carbohydrates":"29.2 g","calories":"1142 kJ \/ 272 kcal"},"usefulItems":"small bowl , 12-hole muffin tray, 12 cupcake liners, wooden skewer, wire rack, oven","hintsAndTricks":["This recipe uses coarse polenta. Do not use the quick-cooking variety.","If you’re lime doesn’t produce 1 tbsp of juice, then just use extra lemon juice to make up the difference. You need 2 tbsp (40 g) total of citrus juice for these polenta cakes."],"basicInfo":["easy","10m","40m","12 portions"]}